## Building libcudf

Whenever building libcudf from scratch (CMake has not been run before), run:

```bash
export CUDAARCHS=NATIVE ; build-cudf-cpp
```

Note that the `build-cudf-cpp` script is located at `/usr/bin` if you can't find it.

If this is an incremental build, you can just navigate to `/home/coder/cudf/cpp/build/latest` and run: 

```bash
ninja
```

Remember, we are in a devcontainer and don't really want to run the `build.sh` script located at `/home/coder` or install anything ourselves. Instead we always want to use `rapids-*`, `build-*` scripts located at `/usr/bin`.

## Building pylibcudf and cudf python
For example, you can build pylibcudf and cudf python as:

```bash
build-cudf-cpp ; build-pylibcudf-python ; build-cudf-python
```

Note that `build-pylibcudf-python` must always successfully run before running `build-cudf-python` or there will be errors

# Clean up
Similar to build instructions, we can use `clean-cudf-cpp` or `clean-cudf-python` etc. scripts located at `/usr/bin`.

## CMake fatal error handling
If we run into a fatal CMake error at the very start of CMake while building libcudf (stating packages mismatched), it's like because our packages are outdated, we can just update them using:

```bash
rapids-make-<ENV>-env
```

where `<ENV>` is either `pip` or `conda` depending on the type of the devcontainer we currently are in. Some users may specify this as a part of their workspace name. i.e., the `.code-workspace` file's name located at `/home/coder` so you can use that. Otherwise, prompt me to specify which devcontainer we are using.

## Running Google tests

Run relevant Google tests 

```bash
cd /home/coder/cudf/cpp/build/latest ; ./gtests/<TEST_NAME>_TEST
```

## Running Pytests

Make sure to build pylibcudf and python before running any of these.

Pylibcudf tests are located here: `/home/coder/cudf/python/pylibcudf/tests` and you can use `py.test` to run them. Example:

```bash
cd /home/coder/cudf/python/pylibcudf/tests/io ; py.test test_parquet.py
```

Similarly, cudf-python tests are located here: `/home/coder/cudf/python/cudf/cudf/tests` and can be run the same way. Note that the sub-folders contained at this location may have a different name such as `io -> input_output`.
